"""
			####THIS SECTION FOR INFORMATION ONLY####
			#Example Drug Screen Detail data object should look like this:
			{
				"value": {
				  "id": 0
				  "employee_id":0
				  "employee_name": "Susan Jones"
				  "hmis":False
				  "note_trunc":"I really like th..."
				  "note":"I really like this participant"			  
				  "time_created": "07/30/2020",
				 	 }
				"style": {
				      "classes" = "Table/Cell_Detail"
					  }
				}
		####END INFORMATION####
			
		####BEGIN ACTUAL SCRIPT####
	"""
	import traceback
	try:
		#table_data is the data object to return
		table_data = []
			
		#Iterate over the results of the query
		for row in range(value.getRowCount()):
			row_struct = {}
			row_data = {}
			style = {}	
			#Map query results into correct attributes
			row_data['note_id'] = value.getValueAt(row, "id")
			row_data['time_created'] = value.getValueAt(row, "time_created")	
			row_data['employee_id'] = value.getValueAt(row, "employee_id")
			row_data['employee_name'] = value.getValueAt(row, "employee_name")
			row_data['hmis'] = value.getValueAt(row, "hmis")
			row_data['note_type_id'] = value.getValueAt(row, "note_type_id")
			row_data['note_type'] = value.getValueAt(row, "note_type")
			row_data['note_trunc'] = value.getValueAt(row, "note")[0:80]
			row_data['note'] = value.getValueAt(row, "note")
			#Set the default style for the row
			style['classes'] = "Table/Cell_Detail"
			row_struct['value'] = row_data
			row_struct['style'] = style
			#Append the individual row date to the table data object
			table_data.append(row_struct)
					
		return table_data
	except:
		logger = system.util.getLogger("Participants CaseNotesTableDetail view.custom.notes_data")
		msg = traceback.format_exc()
		logger.error(msg)

import traceback
	try:
		notes_data = value
		project = "RITI"
		#table_data is the data object to return
		services_data = []
				
		if len(notes_data):
			for row in range(len(notes_data)):
				case_note_id = self.custom.notes_data[row].value.note_id
				participant_id = self.params.participantID
				#system.perspective.print('Case Note:' + str(case_note_id) + ' Participant:' + str(participant_id))
				path = "Participants/CaseNotes/CaseNotesServiceSelect"
				parameters = {"case_note_id":case_note_id,
							"participant_id":participant_id,
							"program":"1=1",
							"service":"1=1"}
				services = system.db.runNamedQuery(project=project,path=path,parameters=parameters, getKey=True)
				for service in range(services.getRowCount()):
					row_struct = {}
					row_data = {}
					style = {}	
					#Map query results into correct attributes
					row_data['note_id'] = case_note_id
					row_data['participant_id'] = participant_id
					row_data['service_id'] = services.getValueAt(service, "servicesRowId")
					row_data['employee_id'] = services.getValueAt(service, "employeeId")
					row_data['employee_name'] = services.getValueAt(service, "employeeName")
					row_data['enrollment_id'] = services.getValueAt(service, "programId")
					row_data['enrollment_name'] = services.getValueAt(service, "ProgramName")
					row_data['type_id'] = services.getValueAt(service, "serviceTypeId")
					row_data['service_id'] = services.getValueAt(service, "serviceId")
					row_data['service_name'] = services.getValueAt(service, "serviceName")
					if services.getValueAt(service, "HMIS") == True:
						row_data['HMIS'] = 1
					elif services.getValueAt(service, "HMIS") == False:
						row_data['HMIS'] = 0
					else:
						row_data['HMIS'] = None
					row_data['quantity'] = services.getValueAt(service, "quantity")
					row_data['comment'] = services.getValueAt(service, "comment")
					#Set the default style for the row
					style['classes'] = "Table/Cell_Detail"
					row_struct['value'] = row_data
					row_struct['style'] = style
					#Append the individual row date to the table data object
					services_data.append(row_struct)
							
			return services_data

		else:
			return None
	except:
		logger = system.util.getLogger("Participants CaseNotesTableDetail view.custom.services_data")
		msg = traceback.format_exc()
		logger.error(msg)

import traceback
	try:
		notes_data = value
		services_data = []
		if self.custom.services_data != None:
			services_data = self.custom.services_data
		#system.perspective.print(str(len(services_data)) + ' services found')
		#if len(services_data) < 1:
			#services_data = []
		table_data = []
		#Move the date from the case notes directly to the table
		if len(notes_data):
			for row in range(len(notes_data)):
				row_struct = {}
				note = {}
				service_list = []
				style = {}	
				#Map query results into correct attributes
				#system.perspective.print('Table Data Processing Case Note' + str(notes_data[row].value.note_id))
				note['note_id'] = notes_data[row].value.note_id
				note['time_created'] = notes_data[row].value.time_created
				note['employee_id'] = notes_data[row].value.employee_id
				note['employee_name'] = notes_data[row].value.employee_name
				note['hmis'] = notes_data[row].value.hmis
				note['note_type_id'] = notes_data[row].value.note_type_id
				note['note_type'] = notes_data[row].value.note_type
				note['note'] = notes_data[row].value.note
				note['note_trunc'] = notes_data[row].value.note_trunc
				note['service_desc'] = ''
				RowNumber = 0
				#system.perspective.print(str(len(services_data)) + ' services found')
				if len(services_data):
					for s_row in range(len(services_data)):
						service = {}
						#system.perspective.print(str(note['note_id']) + ' ' + str(services_data[s_row].value.note_id))
						if note['note_id'] == services_data[s_row].value.note_id:
							#system.perspective.print('Table Data Processing Service' + str(services_data[s_row].value.service_id))
							service['participant_id'] = services_data[s_row].value.participant_id
							service['employee_id'] = services_data[s_row].value.employee_id
							service['employee_name'] = services_data[s_row].value.employee_name
							service['enrollment_id'] = services_data[s_row].value.enrollment_id
							service['enrollment_name'] = services_data[s_row].value.enrollment_name
							service['type_id'] = services_data[s_row].value.type_id
							service['service_id'] = services_data[s_row].value.service_id
							service['service_name'] = services_data[s_row].value.service_name
							service['HMIS'] = services_data[s_row].value.HMIS
							service['quantity'] = services_data[s_row].value.quantity
							service['comment'] = services_data[s_row].value.comment
							service['row_num'] = RowNumber
							note['service_desc'] = note['service_desc'] + service['service_name'] + ", "
							service_list.append(service)
							RowNumber += 1
				#Set the default style for the row
				style['classes'] = "Table/Cell_Detail"
				#note['services'] = service_list
				row_struct['value'] = note
				row_struct['services'] = service_list
				row_struct['style'] = style
				#Append the individual row date to the table data object
				table_data.append(row_struct)
	
		return table_data
	except:
		logger = system.util.getLogger("Participants CaseNotesTableDetail view.custom.table_data")
		msg = traceback.format_exc()
		logger.error(msg)
